# Tests + coverage

- **New or changed behavior** → add or update tests in `tests/` (`test_*.py`). No merge of untested logic unless user says skip tests for this change.
- **Coverage floor: 80%** line coverage on the package/modules you touch; project-wide goal same — do not drop total below 80% when adding code.
- **Tooling:** use `pytest` + `pytest-cov` via **uv** (`uv run pytest …`). Typical check:

  `uv run pytest --cov=<import_name> --cov-report=term-missing --cov-fail-under=80`

  Replace `<import_name>` with real package dir (e.g. `pi_agent_lm` once layout exists) or `main` for single-file stage.

- If `pyproject.toml` has no test deps yet, add dev deps (`pytest`, `pytest-cov`) so coverage gate can run. Wire `[tool.pytest.ini_options]` / `[tool.coverage.run]` when layout stabilizes.
- **README:** when test/coverage commands exist, put them under `## How to run` (or `## Tests`) per other project rule.
